label: Chronology
definition: The age of a specimen or related materials that is generated from a dating assay.

label: Chronology ID
definition: An identifier for the set of information associated with a Chronology.

label: Maximum Age
definition: The upper limit for the age of a specimen as determined by a dating method.

label: Maximum Age Units
definition: The units associated with the maximumAge.

label: Minimum Age
definition: The lower limit for the age of a specimen as determined by a dating method.

label: Minimum Age Units
definition: The units associated with the minimumAge.

label: Age Uncertainty
definition: "The assessed temporal uncertainty in the maximum or minimum age estimates, or overall uncertainty for both."

label: Age Uncertainty Method
definition: The method used to generate reported uncertainty calculations.

label: Material Dated
definition: A description of the material on which the dating protocol was actually performed.

label: Material Dated ID
definition: An identifier for the material on which the dating protocol was performed.

label: Chronology Protocol
definition: A description or reference to the methods used to determine the presented chronology data.

label: Chronology Remarks
definition: Notes or comments about the chronology determination.

label: Chronology References
definition: "A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, bibliographic reference, global unique identifier, URI) of literature associated with the chronology determination of a specimen."
